## Runtime data services (courtesy)

When the relevant features are enabled, Nexus queries the external services
below at runtime. **None of their data is redistributed with the app**, and
each is used under its own terms of service. These acknowledgments are given as
a courtesy to the operators and communities who provide them:

- **SatNOGS DB** (<https://db.satnogs.org>) — which amateur satellites and
  transponders are active, for the Satellites feature. SatNOGS DB data is
  provided by the SatNOGS / Libre Space Foundation community under
  **CC BY-SA 4.0**. Data courtesy of the SatNOGS project and its contributors.
- **CelesTrak** (<https://celestrak.org>, T.S. Kelso) — amateur-satellite
  TLE / GP orbital elements.
- **wspr.live** (the community mirror of wsprnet.org) — WSPR beacon reception
  evidence for the "getting out" check; free non-commercial terms. Data
  courtesy of wspr.live / wsprnet.org contributors.
- **PSK Reporter** (Philip Gladstone) — reception-report retrieval and
  outbound spotting.
- **Reverse Beacon Network** — CW/digital skimmer spots.
- **NOAA SWPC** (services.swpc.noaa.gov) — solar flux, K-index, X-ray/proton
  flux, aurora, solar-wind, and alert feeds (US government, **public domain**).
- **prop.kc2g.com** (Andrew Rodland, KC2G) — real-time MUF map.
- **WA7BNM Contest Calendar** (<https://www.contestcalendar.com/>, Bruce Horn
  WA7BNM) — the upcoming-contests pane.
- **NG3K Announced DX Operations** (Bill Feidt, NG3K) — DXpedition calendar.
- **Parks on the Air (POTA)** and **Summits on the Air (SOTA)** — activator
  spot APIs.
- **HamQTH** (<https://www.hamqth.com/>, Petr Hlozek OK2CQR) — callsign lookup
  and QSO auto-fill fallback.
- **ARRL Logbook of the World (LoTW)**, **ClubLog** (Michael Wells, G7VJR),
  **QRZ.com**, **eQSL.cc**, and **HRDLog** — callsign lookup and QSL / log
  synchronization for the connectors the operator opts into.

